@model EmailTemplating.SampleData.Customer

@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Templates";
}

<h2>@ViewBag.Title</h2>

<p><strong>@Html.ActionLink("View the Template Grid", "Grid")</strong></p>

<p>
    A message template is used to customize emails sent to individuals.  Each template consists of a <code>body</code> that includes one or more <code>merge tags</code>.  
    These tags are then replaced with data using a map (<code>MergeVarMap</code>) to link the tag with a property in a data model.  The follow is an example of a template
    with three merge tags:
</p>
<pre>
Dear *|name|*,

So good to talk with you *|dow|*.  Let me know if you need more information on our *|product_line|*.  It sounds as if we can really help your organization.

All the best,
Jim
</pre>

<p>
    The merge map might look something like this...
</p>

<table class="table table-bordered" style="width: 400px;">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Variable</th>
            <th>Propery</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>name</td>
            <td>FirstName</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>dow</td>
            <td>ContactDay</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>product_line</td>
            <td>Product</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>@Html.ActionLink("More on MergeVarMap", "Index", "MergeTagMaps")</strong></p>

